The paper deals with the complexity of safety verification for concurrent programs, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of kernels and the Exponential Time Hypothesis (ETH) suggests a connection to computational complexity theory and data structures (cs.DS). The algorithms presented in the paper involve fixed-parameter tractability, which is a topic in parameterized complexity (cs.PL). The study of concurrent programs and their verification is also relevant to the subfield of concurrency theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with the verification of safety properties, which is a topic in formal methods (cs.FL).
